{"ts":"2026-06-26T07:41:43.843Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Planning the Upgrade**\n\nI'm now focusing on the upgrade project, specifically the /contact, /portal, /portal/control-center, /client, and /client/control-center pages. The landing page is off-limits. I'm taking a close look at the specifications.\n\n\n**Analyzing Contact Requirements**\n\nI've been drilling down into the requirements for the /contact page specifically. I was thrown by the initial import of `CompanyContactPage`. It looks like I need to build a custom, secure page directly in `app/contact/page.tsx`, and I will handle all pathways there: Talk To Sales, Book Workshop, Book Consultation, Sales, Support, Partnership, Media, University, Investors, Become Partner, and Careers.\n\n\n**Designing the Pathways**\n\nI'm now designing the interactive pathway selector for the `/contact` page. I'm imagining a clean, modern UI where users click pathways like \"Talk to Sales\" or \"Book Workshop,\" and then a premium form or instructions appear tailored to that specific pathway. This fulfills the UI Quality Constitution's requirements for an interactive selector and a premium CTA section. Now, I'm shifting focus to the `/portal` pages.\n\n\n**Defining Portal Modules**\n\nI'm now defining the structure of the `/portal` pages, envisioning a modular dashboard, possibly as a grid or side-nav. I'm imagining a bento grid or tabbed view for 12 modules, and am listing those modules, their status, metadata, or interactive panels. I'm focusing on the optimal display of these modules.\n\nI'm also considering the design of the `/portal/control-center` and `/client/control-center` pages, which I think may be identical. I want preview modules for Agent Health, Delivery, Spend, Adoption, and Governance, with no fake metrics. I want secure UI and clean forms.\n\n\n"}}
